Yeah, I mean, my job is to read the book.

38:34.654 --> 38:40.841
My job is to read the book, and to ask you to do my work for me.

38:40.901 --> 38:41.241
Yeah.

38:41.845 --> 38:48.055
No, I guess my hope is that people do open the cover.

38:48.135 --> 38:53.304
And I feel that if they will open the cover and just start reading, they'll get carried along.

38:53.384 --> 38:57.010
So you must have a great feeling of satisfaction.

38:57.030 --> 38:57.631
Yeah, I do.

38:58.893 --> 39:00.355
I do.

39:00.776 --> 39:03.761
It's also kind of an out-of-body experience.

39:03.781 --> 39:08.629
It's a little hard to process while it's happening because I lived alone with it.

39:08.896 --> 39:11.921
for so long and I knew it really meant a lot to me.

39:12.101 --> 39:12.942
You never despaired.

39:13.483 --> 39:14.084
No, I didn't.

39:14.124 --> 39:15.085
You knew it would be finished.

39:16.027 --> 39:17.429
I knew I would finish it.

39:17.809 --> 39:21.615
I wondered how the heck old am I going to be when I finish this.

39:21.715 --> 39:35.396
But I did wonder if... I trusted in my feelings about it that it really was important for me and that I would be able to tell the story to friends and family and that it wouldn't be meaningful for them.

39:35.416 --> 39:37.519
But I didn't know if it would be beyond

39:37.752 --> 40:01.448
my circle and uh you know to have diane or me my editor um call and have her say wow i mean that was an incredible experience but it wasn't just me it wasn't just in my head and heart but it was something to touch everybody so just if you could give me the numbers how many letters are there all together and and

40:01.681 --> 40:27.385
yeah um saved in the collection in the collection that i have is about 750 and there are about 500 of them yeah yeah and i really think dm was a great help we really wanted i very much wanted to hit every subject everything that's in that course there's nothing i wanted to leave out that's great yeah so with 500 we were able to get it all in

